name: Greek Spinach and Cheese Quiche Squares
author: Cracker Barrel
summary: If you're a fan of spinach quiche, spanakopita or any version of Greek-inspired spinach-and-feta pie, chances are you'll like these easy-to-make squares.
ingredients: 2 (300 g) packages frozen chopped spinach, thawed, squeezed dry
2 cups CRACKER BARREL Crumbled Feta Cheese with Oregano, Sun Dried Tomatoes and Black Pepper
2 cups CRACKER BARREL Shredded Old Cheddar Cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C)
Bake butter in 9-inch square baking dish 2 minutes or until melted
Remove dish from oven; brush butter onto bottom and sides of dish
Beat eggs with mixer in large bowl
Add flour, milk and baking powder; mix until blended
Stir in spinach, cheeses and onion
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting into squares
